  "texts": [
    "In fact, one of the only mentions of percentiles is in a footnote, where the authors state, in passing: \"Using a percentile chart from a recent exam administration (which is generally available online), ChatGPT would receive a score below the 10th percentile of testtakers while GPT-4 would receive a combined score approaching the 90th percentile of test-takers\".",
    "As explained by JD Advising (n.d.-b), The National Conference of Bar Examiners (NCBE), the organization that writes the Uniform Bar Exam (UBE) does not release UBE percentiles.",
    "5 Because there is no official percentile chart for UBE, all generally available online estimates are unofficial.",
    "Perhaps the most prominent of such estimates are the percentile charts from pre-July 2019 Illinois bar exam.",
    "Pre-2019, 6 Illinois, unlike other states, provided percentile charts of their own exam that allowed UBE test-takers to estimate their approximate percentile given the similarity between the two exams (JD Advising n.d.-b)."
  ],
